In winsafe::co

Struct winsafe::co::ERROR

source [−]
#[repr(transparent)]
pub struct ERROR(_);
This is supported on crate feature kernel only.
Expand description

A native system error code (u32) retrieved by GetLastError function.

Implements the standard Error trait.

Implements the Debug and Display traits to show the error code along with the error description, taken from FormattedError trait. For example, the code below:

use winsafe::prelude::*;
use winsafe::co::ERROR;

println!("{}", ERROR::OUT_OF_PAPER);

Will print:

[0x001c 28] The printer is out of paper.
